Much as I enjoyed this in the crit stage, I still feel it needs trimming, especially in the interview sections. You over-detail the visual elements, taking the reader out of the dialogue flow. In future, try to describe the qualities of the scene during natural pauses in the conversation. Let the reader shift more seamlessly between the various sensory elements of a scene, from visual to auditory to ofactory, etc.

Beyond that, I really enjoyed this. It dragged on, but the core content kept me invested. +1







